      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine flour, yeast, salt, and sugar. Add warm milk, egg yolks, vanilla, and rum and mix to a rough dough. Knead for 10 minutes until smooth. Work in the soft butter a piece at a time; knead for a further 6 to 8 minutes until the dough is smooth, satiny, and pulls away cleanly from the bowl. Cover and leave for 60 minutes until doubled.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape and prove",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Divide into 12 pieces (about 90 g each). Shape each into a smooth ball, pressing a small indent in the centre and placing a teaspoon of jam inside, then sealing and re-rolling into a smooth ball. Alternatively, fill after frying. Arrange on lined trays, cover with oiled film, and prove for 50 minutes until puffed.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fry and glaze",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oil to 175°C. Fry 3 at a time for 3 to 4 minutes per side until deep mahogany brown. Drain briefly on paper. Mix the icing sugar with enough warm water for a pourable glaze. Dip the top of each warm paczek in the glaze or drizzle over. If filling after frying, push a piping nozzle into the side and pipe in the jam while still warm.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
